correctness.rationale: Major schema violations and factual inconsistencies are present. Key issues: (1) Schema misuse/nesting: processParameters.required fields (dosingTime, purgeTime, flowRates, saturation, nucleationPeriod, filmThickness) were incorrectly placed inside thicknessControl; growthPerCycle expects Length (Å) but time values were provided; nucleationPeriod contains nulls; many fields (uniformity, conformality, roughness, filmDensity, flowRates, opticalProperties, onOffRatio) include nulls, violating the schema and the no-empty-values requirement. (2) Unit errors: dosing and purge times were reported in milliseconds with second-level numeric values (e.g., 1.5 ms instead of 1.5 s = 1500 ms; 25 ms instead of 25 s = 25000 ms). (3) Factual mismatch in co-reactant selection: the device metrics (μFE 106.5 cm2/Vs, VTH -0.47 V, SS 113.5 mV/dec) correspond to the IG*ZO split (Ga2O3 with N2O plasma, 5 s), but the coReactant list sets N2O for In2O3 instead of Ga2O3; the N2O plasma time (5 s) is not captured anywhere. (4) numberofCycles set to 20 without source support (the article defines a 20-step supercycle but does not report total cycles used to reach 10 nm); saturation=True is asserted without evidence. (5) Film composition errors: atomicRatio given as 1:1:1 (XPS) contradicts the reported indium-rich composition (e.g., XRF In 71.2%, Ga 7.8%, Zn 21.0%); characterization method should be XRF for cation composition, not XPS. (6) Missing multiple processes: the article reports a reference O2 process and three selective N2O splits (each with 1 s and 5 s), but only one mixed process was extracted. Corrections needed: place required properties at correct schema levels; supply GPC in Å or omit if unknown; fix all time units to ms with correct values; align co-reactant assignment and N2O plasma time with the chosen split; remove unsupported assertions (saturation, numberofCycles) or justify; provide correct composition (from XRF) and method; avoid nulls by omitting optional fields or populating with traceable values; represent each distinct process separately.

completeness.rationale: The extraction is largely incomplete and contains several schema violations and factual inconsistencies. (1) Missing processes: The article reports multiple IGZO ALD conditions: reference O2 plasma (all subcycles), global N2O plasma (1 s and 5 s), and three selective N2O splits for In, Ga, and Zn (each at 1 s and 5 s). Only one process instance is provided, so the dataset does not capture all reported processes. (2) Internal inconsistency: Device metrics (μ_FE=106.5 cm2/V·s, V_TH=-0.47 V, SS=113.5 mV/dec) correspond to the Ga-selective N2O 5 s (IG*ZO) case (Table 1), but reactantSelection specifies N2O for In2O3 and O2 for Ga2O3/ZnO (I*GZO). (3) Schema violations and wrong units: growthPerCycle must be length/ANGSTROM but was populated with dosing times (Time) for each compound; dosingTime and purgeTime use units MilliSEC with values given in seconds (1.5, 25, 10), creating 1000× errors; nucleationPeriod has null numeric/unit; flowRates contain null numeric values; many materialProperties (optical, electrical, uniformity, conformality, roughness, filmDensity, elementalConcentration) are set to nulls—these violate required numeric/unit structures. (4) Incorrect composition: filmComposition.atomicRatio is set to '1:1:1' with XPS, conflicting with XRF cation composition (In 71.2%, Ga 7.8%, Zn 21.0%) reported in Tables S3–S4 and misattributing the method. (5) Process details mismatches/omissions: co-reactant plasma exposure times (O2=1 s; N2O=1 or 5 s) per cation are not correctly reflected; the supercycle count (18:1:1) is correct, but 'numberofCycles'=20 appears to conflate supercycle composition with total cycles (not reported); substrate is set to Si wafer from single-oxide depositions, while the IGZO active layer for TFTs was deposited on a 100 nm SiO2 buffer—should be corrected. Properties to add/review: represent each distinct process as separate objects (reference, global N2O at 1 and 5 s, and three selective splits at 1 and 5 s); fix coReactant assignments and plasma exposure times per cation; correct units and quantity kinds (use ANGSTROM for growthPerCycle; convert seconds to MilliSEC or use correct unit); remove null-valued optional fields or populate with article values; update film composition using XRF values and proper method; correct substrate for the TFT IGZO deposition; align device metrics with the matching process.
